Cite.Verse:
I will declare the decree, the LORD hath said unto me:
Thou art my Son;
this day have I begotten thee.

Chapter.Paragraph:
I have never been contented reading the entire Bible many times, but in addition, in the many times I have read it, I have tried to read it in as many different translations as possible. In that way, I have read
the Reina-Valera the old version (which is the best); I have read the
Scio de San Miguel (which is the best among the Catholic Bibles); I have read
Nácar-Colunga; the photographic copy of the translation of
Casiodoro de Reina only, before the revision by Cipriano Valera, which was printed in 1573; the translation by
Torres Amat;
the photographic copy of the original Cipriano de Valera version, printed in 1602; I have read the
Reina-Valera printed in 1855; the
Russellists version;
the New American Standard, in English;
the King James Version, also in English which is the best English one; the
New King James Version;
the modern version;
the Hebrew Old Testament translated to Spanish by Rabbis; the
Reina-Valera 1960 version;
the Chronological Bible; and I can’t remember how many other versions, not counting how many times I have repeated the reading of the before mentioned versions. And when I say that I have read these versions, I am saying from Genesis to Revelations, as I always do, without skipping over anything. This is not counting the “sacred” books of the Seventh Day Adventists, the Mormons, Armstrong’s World Wide Church, the Russellites, the Koran, etc.
